The paper deals with the synthesis of large-scale IoT networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses optimization and constraint satisfaction techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of mixed-integer linear programming and satisfiability modulo convex optimization also suggests that the paper could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the use of elastic computing resources, which is relevant to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
